Your toolkit is assembled. The Three Pillars stand ready: your chisel, your hammer, your principle of progression. Your neuro-session ritual is a blank template, waiting for your personal rhythm. You understand the silent, non-negotiable partners of sleep and nourishment. And you now hold your Baseline Scan—the honest, unvarnished map of your starting territory.

The theory is complete. The warm-up is over.

Tomorrow, we step onto the gym floor. We will begin with the most fundamental exercise of all: taming the wild, wandering attention. It will be simple. It will be harder than you think. You will feel the first, faint “burn” of a new neural connection straining to form, and you will learn to recognize it not as a sign of failure, but as the pure sensation of growth.

Your mind is the marble. Your will is the hand. The tools are in your grip.

Are you prepared to feel the burn?